## Sprint 3 — Summary

### Backend (BE)

**BE-3.1 — Pipeline state API**
- `pause/route.ts` — running → paused
- `resume/route.ts` — paused → running
- `cancel/route.ts` — running|paused → cancelled (with AlertDialog confirmation pattern)
- Updated `execute/route.ts` — now also allows `failed` pipelines to re-execute, and points to the new enhanced simulator
- Updated `[id]/route.ts` — GET now includes sessions join for progress data

**BE-3.2 — Logs API** (`pipelines/[id]/logs/route.ts`)
- Cursor-based pagination (keyset via `created_at`)
- Filters: `agent_id`, `level`, `limit` (max 200)
- Resolves logs via latest session for the pipeline

**BE-3.3 — Token management** (`sessions/[id]/tokens/route.ts`)
- PATCH with `{ tokensToAdd }`, increments usage, sets session `status=warning` at ≥90%

**BE-3.4 — Enhanced simulator** (`lib/simulator/agent-simulator.ts`)
- Configurable speed (slow/normal/fast: 3000/1000/300ms)
- Realistic Korean log messages per role (pm, engineer, reviewer, planner, tester)
- Progressive progress + token updates per log step
- Sample `code_changes` inserted on completion
- `stopSimulation()` for cancellation
- `api/dev/simulate/route.ts` — dev-only POST/DELETE endpoint

### Frontend (FE)

**FE-3.1 — Monitoring page** (`pipelines/[id]/page.tsx`)
- 3-tier layout: title+status badge → overall progress bar → agent grid
- Session token gauge, action bar, togglable log viewer

**FE-3.2 — AgentStatusCard** — animated status indicator (ping animation for active), progress bar, role icon, token usage tooltip

**FE-3.3 — SessionLifetimeGauge** — 4-color policy (green/yellow/orange/red), inline warnings, sonner Toast at 80%, AlertDialog modal at 90%

**FE-3.4 — `usePipelineRealtime`** — 3 Supabase Realtime channels (pipeline/agents/logs), connection status tracking, automatic cleanup

**FE-3.5 — LogViewer** — virtual scroll via `@tanstack/react-virtual` (handles 10k+ logs), auto-scroll toggle, debounced search, agent/level filters

**FE-3.6 — PipelineControls** — Pause/Resume/Cancel buttons, cancel requires AlertDialog confirmation, loading states, error toasts

